uds1ConfigTable.name: uds1ConfigTable
uds1ConfigTable.description: This table is an extension of the ds1ConfigTable in the DS1 MIB defined by RFC1232.

uds1ConfigEntry.name: uds1ConfigEntry
uds1ConfigEntry.description: This table contains configurable parameters for a CSU that are not supported in the DS1 MIB defined by RFC1232. Each entry in this table corresponds to an entry in the DS1 MIB. There is a one-to-one correspondance between the value of uds1CSUIndex and ds1CSUIndex.

uds1CfgIndex.name: uds1CfgIndex
uds1CfgIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value corresponds to ds1CSUIndex in the DS1 MIB defined in RFC1232. The value of uds1CfgIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

uds1CfgRespToRemoteLoopbk.name: uds1CfgRespToRemoteLoopbk
uds1CfgRespToRemoteLoopbk.description: This object configures the specified CSU to either ignore or respond to remotely initiated loopback requests.

uds1CfgJitterAttenuation.name: uds1CfgJitterAttenuation
uds1CfgJitterAttenuation.description: This object is used to select how the jitter attenuation circuit on the CSU is to be used. It can be used to attenuate jitter on the receiver, or the transmitter.

uds1CfgXmitLineBuildOut.name: uds1CfgXmitLineBuildOut
uds1CfgXmitLineBuildOut.description: This object is used to configure the amount of attenuation that is to be applied to the transmit signal in order to control cross-talk, etc.

uds1CfgAutoBusyEnable.name: uds1CfgAutoBusyEnable
uds1CfgAutoBusyEnable.description: This object is used to enable or disable the automatic busy out feature for all timeslots on the specified CSU. If enabled, when a modem is considered idle and that modem is not sending the idle pattern to the T1 Card on the TDM bus, the timeslot will be busied out.

uds1CfgDialInAdr.name: uds1CfgDialInAdr
uds1CfgDialInAdr.description: This object identifies whether or not DNIS digits will be transferred as part of the call setup for the specified T1 line.

uds1CfgZeroCoding.name: uds1CfgZeroCoding
uds1CfgZeroCoding.description: This object defines the type of zero coding used on the specified DS1. It provides some values that are not present in the experimental DS1 MIB.

uds1CfgDialInOutTrunkSt.name: uds1CfgDialInOutTrunkSt
uds1CfgDialInOutTrunkSt.description: This will set the Dial-in/Dial-out trunk start signal type. Default = wink(1).

uds1CfgDialInAdrAckWinkEn.name: uds1CfgDialInAdrAckWinkEn
uds1CfgDialInAdrAckWinkEn.description: Allows to enable/disable an acknowledgement wink after the dial-in address information has been received.

uds1CfgDialOutAdrDly.name: uds1CfgDialOutAdrDly
uds1CfgDialOutAdrDly.description: Allows an adjustable delay on sending out address information from the T1 NAC to the TELCO.

uds1CfgStuffByteValue.name: uds1CfgStuffByteValue
uds1CfgStuffByteValue.description: The stuffed byte to send to TELCO for inactive DS0 in Fractional T1.

uds1CfgDialInOutTrunkType.name: uds1CfgDialInOutTrunkType
uds1CfgDialInOutTrunkType.description: This will set the Dial-In/Dial-out trunk type. Default = eAndMTypeII(1).

uds1CfgPriSwitchType.name: uds1CfgPriSwitchType
uds1CfgPriSwitchType.description: This sets the primary switch type for the T1-PRI ISDN NAC. The setting takes effect at NAC boot time. Default = priSw5ESS(2).

uds1CfgIdleByte.name: uds1CfgIdleByte
uds1CfgIdleByte.description: This sets the idle byte pattern for the T1-PRI ISDN NAC. The setting takes effect at NAC boot time. Default = 0xFE.

uds1CfgAnlgBlockErrCode.name: uds1CfgAnlgBlockErrCode
uds1CfgAnlgBlockErrCode.description: This is the error code that will be returned to an ISDN switch when analog connections are being blocked. Default = 58.

uds1CfgDgtlBlockErrCode.name: uds1CfgDgtlBlockErrCode
uds1CfgDgtlBlockErrCode.description: This is the error code that will be returned to an ISDN switch when digital connections are being blocked. Default = 58.

uds1CfgNoMdmAvailErrCode.name: uds1CfgNoMdmAvailErrCode
uds1CfgNoMdmAvailErrCode.description: This is the error code that will be returned to an ISDN switch when there are no modems available to accept the requested connection. Default = 58.

uds1CfgNoIgwsAvailErrCode.name: uds1CfgNoIgwsAvailErrCode
uds1CfgNoIgwsAvailErrCode.description: This is the error code that will be returned to an ISDN switch when no IGWS connections are available. Default = 58.

uds1CfgChanBlockErrCode.name: uds1CfgChanBlockErrCode
uds1CfgChanBlockErrCode.description: This is the error code that will be returned to an ISDN switch when connections to a specific B channel are being blocked. Default = 58.

uds1CfgBlockCallType.name: uds1CfgBlockCallType
uds1CfgBlockCallType.description: This object determines if a PRI span line will block calls of a specific type. This object does not apply to a NAC operating in Rob Bit T1 mode. Default = blockNone(2).

uds1CfgNfasId.name: uds1CfgNfasId
uds1CfgNfasId.description: This defines the NFAS ID associated with a PRI span line. This object does not apply to Rob Bit T1 operation. Default = 0.

uds1CfgNfasDChannel.name: uds1CfgNfasDChannel
uds1CfgNfasDChannel.description: This determines how a PRI span line will use the DS0 normally assigned as a D channel when NFAS is being used. This object does not apply to Rob Bit T1 operation. Default = dchannel(2).

uds1CfgShrtHaulDist.name: uds1CfgShrtHaulDist
uds1CfgShrtHaulDist.description: Variuos distance ranges supported by Short Haul NIC Default=len0thru133Ft.

uds1CfgCallProceedingRsp.name: uds1CfgCallProceedingRsp
uds1CfgCallProceedingRsp.description: This object determines to send CALL_PROCEEDING and CONNECT response, when a SETUP message is received from TELCO. Default = ON.

uds1CfgAlertingRsp.name: uds1CfgAlertingRsp
uds1CfgAlertingRsp.description: This object determines to send ALERTING response, when a SETUP message is received from TELCO. Default = OFF.

uds1CfgServiceState.name: uds1CfgServiceState
uds1CfgServiceState.description: This objects configures the service state of the DS1 and will configure the state for power up if saved to NVRAM. Default= inService(2).

uds1CfgIcbKeyword.name: uds1CfgIcbKeyword
uds1CfgIcbKeyword.description: This is the keyword used for DASS2 Incoming Call Barring control.

uds1CfgOverlapRxMode.name: uds1CfgOverlapRxMode
uds1CfgOverlapRxMode.description: This object allows dialed digits to arrive in separate messages. Default = disabled(2)

uds1CfgEandMnoAddrTimer.name: uds1CfgEandMnoAddrTimer
uds1CfgEandMnoAddrTimer.description: This object is for E&M type II trunks with no DNIS address. If timer is >0, the ch T1 NAC will flush calls upon timer expiration, if the modem has not signalled the NAC to go ahead and answer the call. 2 seconds per unit. Default = 0

uds1CfgSeizureWinkDly.name: uds1CfgSeizureWinkDly
uds1CfgSeizureWinkDly.description: Allows an adjustable delay on sending out address information from the T1 NAC to the TELCO. Default=18.

uds1IntervalTable.name: uds1IntervalTable
uds1IntervalTable.description: An extension of the DS1 Interval table which provides status counters over 15 minute intervals.

uds1IntervalEntry.name: uds1IntervalEntry
uds1IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the extended DS1 Interval table. Every entry in the DS1 Interval table will have a corresponding entry in this table.

uds1IntIndex.name: uds1IntIndex
uds1IntIndex.description: This is the index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of uds1IntIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

uds1IntNumber.name: uds1IntNumber
uds1IntNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minute interval (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).

uds1IntBurstyErrSeconds.name: uds1IntBurstyErrSeconds
uds1IntBurstyErrSeconds.description: This object counts the number of seconds, over the specified interval, in which there were more than 2 and less than 320 CRC errors.

uds1IntFrameBitErrors.name: uds1IntFrameBitErrors
uds1IntFrameBitErrors.description: A specific bit pattern is used for the T1 receiver to determine frame allignment. This object counts the number of incorrectly received framing bits in the specified 15 minute interval.

uds1IntDeltaFrameAlligns.name: uds1IntDeltaFrameAlligns
uds1IntDeltaFrameAlligns.description: This object counts the number of times the specified T1 receiver has reframed on a new framing pattern (ie. due to an OOF condition) in the specified 15 minute interval.

uds1IntExcessCRCErrors.name: uds1IntExcessCRCErrors
uds1IntExcessCRCErrors.description: This object counts each time 32 of any 33 consecutive CRCs are in error for the specified T1 line in the specified 15 minute interval. This counter is only valid in ESF format.

uds1CurrentTable.name: uds1CurrentTable
uds1CurrentTable.description: An extension of the DS1 Current table that provides status counters over the present 15 minute interval.

uds1CurrentEntry.name: uds1CurrentEntry
uds1CurrentEntry.description: An entry in the extended DS1 Current table. Every entry in the DS1 Current table will have a corresponding entry in this table.

uds1CurrIndex.name: uds1CurrIndex
uds1CurrIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of uds1CurrIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

uds1CurrBurstyErrSeconds.name: uds1CurrBurstyErrSeconds
uds1CurrBurstyErrSeconds.description: This object counts the number of seconds, in the current 15 minute interval, during which there was more than two, and less than 320 CRC errors.

uds1CurrFrameBitErrors.name: uds1CurrFrameBitErrors
uds1CurrFrameBitErrors.description: A specific bit pattern is used for the receiver to determine frame allignment. This object is a count of the number of incorrectly received framing bits in the current 15 minute interval.

uds1CurrDeltaFrameAlligns.name: uds1CurrDeltaFrameAlligns
uds1CurrDeltaFrameAlligns.description: This object counts the number of times the specified T1 receiver has reframed on a new framing pattern (ie. due to an OOF condition) in the current 15 minute interval.

uds1CurrExcessCRCErrors.name: uds1CurrExcessCRCErrors
uds1CurrExcessCRCErrors.description: This object counts each time 32 of any 33 consecutive CRCs are in error for the specified T1 line in the current 15 minute interval. This counter is only valid in ESF format.

uds1TotalTable.name: uds1TotalTable
uds1TotalTable.description: An extension of the DS1 Total table that provides the cumulative sum of the various statistics for the 24 hour interval preceding the first valid interval in the uds1CurrentTable.

uds1TotalEntry.name: uds1TotalEntry
uds1TotalEntry.description: An entry in the extended DS1 Total table.

uds1TotIndex.name: uds1TotIndex
uds1TotIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of ds1TotalIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

uds1TotBurstyErrSeconds.name: uds1TotBurstyErrSeconds
uds1TotBurstyErrSeconds.description: This object counts the number of seconds, over the last 24 hour period, in which there were more than 2 and less than 320 CRC errors.

uds1TotFrameBitErrors.name: uds1TotFrameBitErrors
uds1TotFrameBitErrors.description: A specific bit pattern is used so the T1 receiver can determine frame allignment. This object counts the total number of incorrectly received framing bits in the last 24 hour period.

uds1TotDeltaFrameAlligns.name: uds1TotDeltaFrameAlligns
uds1TotDeltaFrameAlligns.description: This object counts the number of times the specified T1 receiver has reframed on a new framing pattern (ie. due to an OOF condition) in the last 24 hour period.

uds1TotExcessCRCErrors.name: uds1TotExcessCRCErrors
uds1TotExcessCRCErrors.description: This object indicates the total number of times there have been 32 of any 33 consecutive CRCs in error on the specified T1 line in the last 24 hour period. This counter is only valid in ESF format.

uds1StatTable.name: uds1StatTable
uds1StatTable.description: USR's DS1 Status table contains various CSU status information. There is no corresponding table in the DS1 MIB defined by RFC1232.

uds1StatEntry.name: uds1StatEntry
uds1StatEntry.description: There is one entry in the DS1 Status table for each CSU in the chassis.

uds1StatIndex.name: uds1StatIndex
uds1StatIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The value of this object matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

uds1StatReceiverGain.name: uds1StatReceiverGain
uds1StatReceiverGain.description: This object identifies the amount of gain applied to boost the receive signal level to an appropriate operating level.

uds1StatOutOfFrame.name: uds1StatOutOfFrame
uds1StatOutOfFrame.description: This object indicates when the framing pattern for the specified T1 line has been lost and data connot be extracted properly. This condition is also known as red alarm.

uds1StatLossOfSignal.name: uds1StatLossOfSignal
uds1StatLossOfSignal.description: This object indicates when 175 consecutive 0's have been detected. The signal is considered recovered if the 1's density reaches 12.5% (ie. four ones in a 32 bit period).

uds1StatReceivingAIS.name: uds1StatReceivingAIS
uds1StatReceivingAIS.description: This object identifies when the remote end of the specified T1 line has lost its receive signal and is transmitting a stream of all 1's to the local end. This AIS condition is also known as blue alarm.

uds1StatSwitchTypeActive.name: uds1StatSwitchTypeActive
uds1StatSwitchTypeActive.description: This object identifies the primary switch type that the T1-PRI ISDN NAC is currently connected to.

uds1StatDchanOperational.name: uds1StatDchanOperational
uds1StatDchanOperational.description: This object reflects the operational status of the D channel on the T1-PRI ISDN NAC.

uds1StatE1ContCrc.name: uds1StatE1ContCrc
uds1StatE1ContCrc.description: This object indicates when continuous CRC errors are being received on the E1 DS1 span line on the T1-PRI ISDN NAC.

uds1StatE1PhysicalState.name: uds1StatE1PhysicalState
uds1StatE1PhysicalState.description: This object reflects the physical state of the E1 DS1 span line on the T1-PRI ISDN NAC.

uds1StatLoopBackInit.name: uds1StatLoopBackInit
uds1StatLoopBackInit.description: This object tells if the loopback was initiated by the network or by command

uds1StatNfasDChannel.name: uds1StatNfasDChannel
uds1StatNfasDChannel.description: This reflect how a PRI span line is using the DS0 normally assigned as a D channel when NFAS is being used. This object does not apply to Rob Bit T1 operation. Default = dchannel(2).

uds1StatDChannel.name: uds1StatDChannel
uds1StatDChannel.description: This is the status of the D channel for this PRI span line. A value of notSupported(1) means that this DS1 is not operating in ISDN mode or there is no D channel defined on this span line.

uds1StatDs0SrvcChngLst.name: uds1StatDs0SrvcChngLst
uds1StatDs0SrvcChngLst.description: This object contains the current list of DS0s that have changed their state from In Service to Out of Service or Vice versa. The list is included in the corresponding SNMP trap.

uds1StatMultiFrame.name: uds1StatMultiFrame
uds1StatMultiFrame.description: This object identifies when the E1/PRI NAC line has lost synchronization with the Time-Slot 16 Multi-Frame alignment pattern. Only valid for E1/CAS NAC.

uds1StatRemMultiFrame.name: uds1StatRemMultiFrame
uds1StatRemMultiFrame.description: This object identifies when the remote end of the specified E1/PRI NAC line has lost synchronization with the Time-Slot 16 Multi-Frame alignment pattern. Only valid for E1/CAS NAC.

uds1StatServiceState.name: uds1StatServiceState
uds1StatServiceState.description: This object shows the current state of the DS1 Service. Default = inService(2).

uds1CmdTable.name: uds1CmdTable
uds1CmdTable.description: The DS1 Command table contains an entry for each of the manageable CSUs in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on one or more CSUs in the chassis.

uds1CmdEntry.name: uds1CmdEntry
uds1CmdEntry.description: There is one entry in the DS1 Command table per CSU in the chassis.

uds1CmdIndex.name: uds1CmdIndex
uds1CmdIndex.description: A unique value for each CSU in the chassis. The value of uds1CmdIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

uds1CmdMgtStationId.name: uds1CmdMgtStationId
uds1CmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the result of that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with uds1CmdReqId and uds1CmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

uds1CmdReqId.name: uds1CmdReqId
uds1CmdReqId.description: This object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command on this DS1 interface. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this object contains the zero value.

uds1CmdFunction.name: uds1CmdFunction
uds1CmdFunction.description: This object identifies the command being requested.

uds1CmdForce.name: uds1CmdForce
uds1CmdForce.description: In some cases, the DS1 interface may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections. In such cases, a command request with uds1CmdForce not defined, or set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, uds1CmdForce can be set to force in a re-issued request and the command will be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

uds1CmdParam.name: uds1CmdParam
uds1CmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no additional parameters required.

uds1CmdResult.name: uds1CmdResult
uds1CmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested command, or the value none(1) if no commands have been requested since the last reset.

uds1CmdCode.name: uds1CmdCode
uds1CmdCode.description: The value of this object upon command completion indicates a further description of what went wrong if the command was unsuccessful.

uds1TrapEnaTable.name: uds1TrapEnaTable
uds1TrapEnaTable.description: A trap enable table that defines a column for every trap that a DS1 entity can generate.

uds1TrapEnaEntry.name: uds1TrapEnaEntry
uds1TrapEnaEntry.description: There is one entry in this table for every CSU that exists in the chassis.

uds1TrapEnaIndex.name: uds1TrapEnaIndex
uds1TrapEnaIndex.description: A unique value for each CSU in the chassis. The value of uds1TrapEnaIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding DS1 entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

uds1TrapEnaYellowAlarm.name: uds1TrapEnaYellowAlarm
uds1TrapEnaYellowAlarm.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a yellow alarm condition on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaRedAlarm.name: uds1TrapEnaRedAlarm
uds1TrapEnaRedAlarm.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a red alarm condition on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaLossOfSignal.name: uds1TrapEnaLossOfSignal
uds1TrapEnaLossOfSignal.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of loss of signal on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaAlarmIndSignal.name: uds1TrapEnaAlarmIndSignal
uds1TrapEnaAlarmIndSignal.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of an alarm indication signal (AIS) on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaYellowAlarmClr.name: uds1TrapEnaYellowAlarmClr
uds1TrapEnaYellowAlarmClr.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a yellow alarm condition being cleared on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaRedAlarmClr.name: uds1TrapEnaRedAlarmClr
uds1TrapEnaRedAlarmClr.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a red alarm condition being cleared on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaLossOfSgnlClr.name: uds1TrapEnaLossOfSgnlClr
uds1TrapEnaLossOfSgnlClr.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of loss of signal condition being cleared on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaAlrmIndSgnlClr.name: uds1TrapEnaAlrmIndSgnlClr
uds1TrapEnaAlrmIndSgnlClr.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of an alarm indication signal (AIS) being cleared on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaContCrcAlrm.name: uds1TrapEnaContCrcAlrm
uds1TrapEnaContCrcAlrm.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a continuous CRC condition on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaContCrcAlrmClr.name: uds1TrapEnaContCrcAlrmClr
uds1TrapEnaContCrcAlrmClr.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of the clearing of a continuous CRC condition on the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaPhysStateChng.name: uds1TrapEnaPhysStateChng
uds1TrapEnaPhysStateChng.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a change in the physical state of the specified DS1.

uds1TrapEnaDchanInSrvc.name: uds1TrapEnaDchanInSrvc
uds1TrapEnaDchanInSrvc.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a change in the service state of a D channel on this span line from Out of Service, Maintenance or Standby to In Service. Default = disableAll(2).

uds1TrapEnaDchanOutOfSrvc.name: uds1TrapEnaDchanOutOfSrvc
uds1TrapEnaDchanOutOfSrvc.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a change in the service state of a D channel on this span line from In Service to Out of Service, Maintenance or Standby. Default = disableAll(2).

uds1TrapEnaDs0InSrvc.name: uds1TrapEnaDs0InSrvc
uds1TrapEnaDs0InSrvc.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a change in the service state of a DS0 on this span line from Out of Service to In Service. Default = disableAll(2).

uds1TrapEnaDs0OutOfSrvc.name: uds1TrapEnaDs0OutOfSrvc
uds1TrapEnaDs0OutOfSrvc.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a change in the service state of a DS0 on this span line from In Service to Out of Service. Default = disableAll(2).

uds1TrapEnaMultiFrame.name: uds1TrapEnaMultiFrame
uds1TrapEnaMultiFrame.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a Multi-Frame Alignment condition on the specified DS1. Default = disableAll(2).

uds1TrapEnaRemMultiFrame.name: uds1TrapEnaRemMultiFrame
uds1TrapEnaRemMultiFrame.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of a Remote Multi-Frame Alignment condition on the specified DS1. Default = disableAll(2).

uds1TrapEnaMultiFrmClr.name: uds1TrapEnaMultiFrmClr
uds1TrapEnaMultiFrmClr.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of clearing a Multi-Frame Alignment condition on the specified DS1. Default = disableAll(2).

uds1TrapEnaRemMultiFrmClr.name: uds1TrapEnaRemMultiFrmClr
uds1TrapEnaRemMultiFrmClr.description: Enable the generation of an SNMP trap upon detection of clearing a Remote Multi-Frame Alignment condition on the specified DS1. Default = disableAll(2).
